%% AutoResolve Demo Scenario Sequence Diagram

%% This diagram illustrates the MVP demo scenario. It maps out the event flow
%% where AutoResolve:
%% - Intercepts a Prometheus memory alert.
%% - Opens a Slack thread for the human on-call.
%% - Utilizes an MCP client to pull Kubernetes logs and identifies the
%%   OOMKilled exception.
%% - Retrieves the appropriate runbook from the Vector DB.
%% - Drafts a GitHub PR to fix the issue and tags the engineer in Slack for
%%   final approval.

sequenceDiagram
    participant P as Prometheus
    participant AR as AutoResolve (Webhook)
    participant Slack as Slack
    participant Agents as LangGraph Swarm
    participant MCP as MCP Servers (Logs/Metrics)
    participant Vector as Vector DB (Runbooks)
    participant Git as GitHub
    
    P->>AR: Fire Alert (High Memory)
    AR->>Slack: Open Incident Thread
    AR->>Agents: Initiate Triage
    Agents->>MCP: Query K8s Logs & Traces
    MCP-->>Agents: Return OOMKilled Exception
    Agents->>Vector: Search similar past incidents
    Vector-->>Agents: Return Runbook for Service X
    Agents->>Git: Draft PR to bump memory limits
    Agents->>Slack: Notify Human with RCA & PR Link
    Slack-->>AR: Human Approves PR